texts.label: paragraph
texts.orig: Although the X1 Carbon has a  much better looking display than the T430s , it still looked a bit washed out when I compared it to other monitors right next to it. The entire display had a weak blue tint and it was difficult to use for extended periods, especially at maximum brightness.
texts.text: Although the X1 Carbon has a  much better looking display than the T430s , it still looked a bit washed out when I compared it to other monitors right next to it. The entire display had a weak blue tint and it was difficult to use for extended periods, especially at maximum brightness.

texts.label: paragraph
texts.orig: A quick Google search took me to a  LaunchPad entry  about a  better ICC profile for the X1 Carbon . After applying the ICC file via GNOME Control Center's Color panel, the display looks fantastic.
texts.text: A quick Google search took me to a  LaunchPad entry  about a  better ICC profile for the X1 Carbon . After applying the ICC file via GNOME Control Center's Color panel, the display looks fantastic.
